<edge source="st.i-ii.q109.a009" target="concept.grace" id="edge.st.i-ii.q109.a009.treated_in.concept.grace">
  <data key="d6">edge.st.i-ii.q109.a009.treated_in.concept.grace</data>
  <data key="d7">st.i-ii.q109.a009</data>
  <data key="d8">I-II q.109 a.9 — Having received grace, can man do good and avoid sin without any further Divine help?</data>
  <data key="d9">article</data>
  <data key="d10">treated_in</data>
  <data key="d11">concept.grace</data>
  <data key="d12">Grace</data>
  <data key="d13">grace</data>
  <data key="d14">structural</data>
  <data key="d15">ann.st-i-ii-q109-a009-treated-in-concept-grace-st-i-ii-q109-a009-resp</data>
  <data key="d16">st.i-ii.q109.a009.resp</data>
  <data key="d17">explicit_textual</data>
  <data key="d18">Secondly, man needs the help of grace in order to be moved by God to act</data>
  <data key="d19"></data>
  <data key="d20"></data>
</edge>
<edge source="st.i-ii.q109.a009" target="concept.perseverance" id="edge.st.i-ii.q109.a009.treated_in.concept.perseverance">
  <data key="d6">edge.st.i-ii.q109.a009.treated_in.concept.perseverance</data>
  <data key="d7">st.i-ii.q109.a009</data>
  <data key="d8">I-II q.109 a.9 — Having received grace, can man do good and avoid sin without any further Divine help?</data>
  <data key="d9">article</data>
  <data key="d10">treated_in</data>
  <data key="d11">concept.perseverance</data>
  <data key="d12">Perseverance</data>
  <data key="d13">act_type</data>
  <data key="d14">structural</data>
  <data key="d15">ann.st-i-ii-q109-a009-treated-in-concept-perseverance-st-i-ii-q109-a009-resp</data>
  <data key="d16">st.i-ii.q109.a009.resp</data>
  <data key="d17">explicit_textual</data>
  <data key="d18">As stated above ( Article 5 ), in order to live righteously a man needs a twofold help of God —first, a habitual gift whereby corrupted human nature is healed, and after being healed is lifted up so as to work deeds meritoriously of everlasting life, which exc</data>
  <data key="d19"></data>
  <data key="d20"></data>
</edge>
<edge source="st.i-ii.q109.a010" target="concept.grace" id="edge.st.i-ii.q109.a010.treated_in.concept.grace">
  <data key="d6">edge.st.i-ii.q109.a010.treated_in.concept.grace</data>
  <data key="d7">st.i-ii.q109.a010</data>
  <data key="d8">I-II q.109 a.10 — Can he of himself persevere in good?</data>
  <data key="d9">article</data>
  <data key="d10">treated_in</data>
  <data key="d11">concept.grace</data>
  <data key="d12">Grace</data>
  <data key="d13">grace</data>
  <data key="d14">structural</data>
  <data key="d15">ann.st-i-ii-q109-a010-treated-in-concept-grace-st-i-ii-q109-a010-resp</data>
  <data key="d16">st.i-ii.q109.a010.resp</data>
  <data key="d17">explicit_textual</data>
  <data key="d18">And in both these ways perseverance is infused together with grace , even as continence and the other virtues are</data>
  <data key="d19"></data>
  <data key="d20"></data>
</edge>
<edge source="st.i-ii.q109.a010" target="concept.perseverance" id="edge.st.i-ii.q109.a010.treated_in.concept.perseverance">
  <data key="d6">edge.st.i-ii.q109.a010.treated_in.concept.perseverance</data>
  <data key="d7">st.i-ii.q109.a010</data>
  <data key="d8">I-II q.109 a.10 — Can he of himself persevere in good?</data>
  <data key="d9">article</data>
  <data key="d10">treated_in</data>
  <data key="d11">concept.perseverance</data>
  <data key="d12">Perseverance</data>
  <data key="d13">act_type</data>
  <data key="d14">structural</data>
  <data key="d15">ann.st-i-ii-q109-a010-treated-in-concept-perseverance-st-i-ii-q109-a010-resp</data>
  <data key="d16">st.i-ii.q109.a010.resp</data>
  <data key="d17">explicit_textual</data>
  <data key="d18">Perseverance is taken in three ways</data>
  <data key="d19"></data>
  <data key="d20"></data>
</edge>
<edge source="st.ii-ii.q001.a001" target="concept.faith" id="edge.st.ii-ii.q001.a001.treated_in.concept.faith">
  <data key="d6">edge.st.ii-ii.q001.a001.treated_in.concept.faith</data>
  <data key="d7">st.ii-ii.q001.a001</data>
  <data key="d8">II-II q.1 a.1 — Is the object of faith the First Truth?</data>
  <data key="d9">article</data>
  <data key="d10">treated_in</data>
  <data key="d11">concept.faith</data>
  <data key="d12">Faith</data>
  <data key="d13">virtue</data>
  <data key="d14">structural</data>
  <data key="d15">ann.st-ii-ii-q001-a001-treated-in-concept-faith-st-ii-ii-q001-a001-resp</data>
  <data key="d16">st.ii-ii.q001.a001.resp</data>
  <data key="d17">explicit_textual</data>
  <data key="d18">Accordingly if we consider, in faith , the formal aspect of the object, it is nothing else than the First Truth</data>
  <data key="d19"></data>
  <data key="d20"></data>
</edge>
<edge source="st.ii-ii.q001.a001" target="concept.first_truth" id="edge.st.ii-ii.q001.a001.treated_in.concept.first_truth">
  <data key="d6">edge.st.ii-ii.q001.a001.treated_in.concept.first_truth</data>
  <data key="d7">st.ii-ii.q001.a001</data>
  <data key="d8">II-II q.1 a.1 — Is the object of faith the First Truth?</data>
  <data key="d9">article</data>
  <data key="d10">treated_in</data>
  <data key="d11">concept.first_truth</data>
  <data key="d12">First Truth</data>
  <data key="d13">object</data>
  <data key="d14">structural</data>
  <data key="d15">ann.st-ii-ii-q001-a001-treated-in-concept-first-truth-st-ii-ii-q001-a001-resp</data>
  <data key="d16">st.ii-ii.q001.a001.resp</data>
  <data key="d17">explicit_textual</data>
  <data key="d18">Accordingly if we consider, in faith , the formal aspect of the object, it is nothing else than the First Truth</data>
  <data key="d19"></data>
  <data key="d20"></data>
</edge>
<edge source="st.ii-ii.q001.a001" target="concept.object_of_faith" id="edge.st.ii-ii.q001.a001.treated_in.concept.object_of_faith">
  <data key="d6">edge.st.ii-ii.q001.a001.treated_in.concept.object_of_faith</data>
  <data key="d7">st.ii-ii.q001.a001</data>
  <data key="d8">II-II q.1 a.1 — Is the object of faith the First Truth?</data>
  <data key="d9">article</data>
  <data key="d10">treated_in</data>
  <data key="d11">concept.object_of_faith</data>
  <data key="d12">Object of Faith</data>
  <data key="d13">doctrine</data>
  <data key="d14">structural</data>
  <data key="d15">ann.st-ii-ii-q001-a001-treated-in-concept-object-of-faith-st-ii-ii-q001-a001-resp</data>
  <data key="d16">st.ii-ii.q001.a001.resp</data>
  <data key="d17">explicit_textual</data>
  <data key="d18">Consequently from this point of view also the object of faith is, in a way, the First Truth, in as much as nothing comes under faith except in relation to God , even as the object of the medical art is health, for it considers nothing save in relation to health.</data>
  <data key="d19"></data>
  <data key="d20"></data>
</edge>
<edge source="st.ii-ii.q001.a002" target="concept.faith" id="edge.st.ii-ii.q001.a002.treated_in.concept.faith">
  <data key="d6">edge.st.ii-ii.q001.a002.treated_in.concept.faith</data>
  <data key="d7">st.ii-ii.q001.a002</data>
  <data key="d8">II-II q.1 a.2 — Is the object of faith something complex or incomplex, i.e. is it a thing or a proposition?</data>
  <data key="d9">article</data>
  <data key="d10">treated_in</data>
  <data key="d11">concept.faith</data>
  <data key="d12">Faith</data>
  <data key="d13">virtue</data>
  <data key="d14">structural</data>
  <data key="d15">ann.st-ii-ii-q001-a002-treated-in-concept-faith-st-ii-ii-q001-a002-resp</data>
  <data key="d16">st.ii-ii.q001.a002.resp</data>
  <data key="d17">explicit_textual</data>
  <data key="d18">Accordingly the object of faith may be considered in two ways</data>
  <data key="d19"></data>
  <data key="d20"></data>
</edge>
<edge source="st.ii-ii.q001.a002" target="concept.object_of_faith" id="edge.st.ii-ii.q001.a002.treated_in.concept.object_of_faith">
  <data key="d6">edge.st.ii-ii.q001.a002.treated_in.concept.object_of_faith</data>
  <data key="d7">st.ii-ii.q001.a002</data>
  <data key="d8">II-II q.1 a.2 — Is the object of faith something complex or incomplex, i.e. is it a thing or a proposition?</data>
  <data key="d9">article</data>
  <data key="d10">treated_in</data>
  <data key="d11">concept.object_of_faith</data>
  <data key="d12">Object of Faith</data>
  <data key="d13">doctrine</data>
  <data key="d14">structural</data>
  <data key="d15">ann.st-ii-ii-q001-a002-treated-in-concept-object-of-faith-st-ii-ii-q001-a002-resp</data>
  <data key="d16">st.ii-ii.q001.a002.resp</data>
  <data key="d17">explicit_textual</data>
  <data key="d18">Accordingly the object of faith may be considered in two ways</data>
